import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='home_score', bins=11, kde=True)
    median_home_score = data['home_score'].median()
    plt.axvline(median_home_score, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Median: {median_home_score:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of home scores?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Home Scores')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    division_counts = data['division'].value_counts()
    sns.barplot(x=division_counts.index, y=division_counts.values)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of matches played by division?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Division")
    plt.ylabel("Number of Matches")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
